[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Python companion for Clinical Trial Patient Matching is excellent. It faithfully implements all four pseudocode stages from the main recipe (structured pre-screen, NLP deep screen, scoring, storage), uses correct boto3 APIs for Comprehend Medical and DynamoDB, properly uses `Decimal` for DynamoDB numeric values, avoids leading slashes in S3 paths, and builds understanding progressively from configuration through multi-stage filtering to final scoring. The synthetic patient data is clinically plausible and demonstrates clear pass/fail scenarios for each criterion type. The code would run without errors given the stated prerequisites and active AWS credentials.
